What is the projected market size & growth rate of the Phosphatases Market?

Market Analysis and Insights:

Global Phosphatases Market

The phosphatases market is likely to reach USD 120.3 million by 2028 and is expected to expand at a compound annual growth rate of 10.10% over the forecast period of 2021 to 2028. The increase in health consciousness among consumers owing to the use of chemicals in agriculture is the factor for the phosphatases market in the forecast period of 2021 to 2028.

Phosphatases are the type of an enzyme which helps to remove a phosphate group from a protein. Phosphatase is a marker of fertility and it also indicates the phosphorus shortage in the soil. In the soil ecosystems, phosphatases play a significant role in the phosphorus cycle (P cycle), which connects to plant growth and P stress (Phosphorus Stress). Also the phosphatases are a good soil quality indicator as their activity reflects the situation of the soil.

The phosphatases market is expected to gain growth, due to the better crop efficiency and enhance crop growth. Also the rapid increase in population and rise in disposable income are also expected to drive the market for phosphatases over the forecast period of 2021 to 2028. The rise in usage particularly for the crop fertility and protection against various pests and diseases and rapid increase consumption of organic food is also likely to lift the growth of the phosphatases market. Also the phosphatase is an indicator of fertility and it also specifies the phosphorus deficiency in the soil which is also the major driving factors leading towards the growth of the phosphatases market.

However, the price fluctuations and strict regulations related to biological products are expected to curb the growth of the phosphatases market in the above mentioned forecast period, whereas the unorganized new entrants with low profit to cost ratio and commercialization of counterfeit of products can challenge the growth of the target market.

In addition, the high demand for the consumption of organic food coupled with various competitive strategies adopted by the key industry participants are expected to accelerate various growth opportunities that will enhance the growth of the phosphatases market in the forecast period of 2021 to 2028.

